tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The laboratory results are largely within normal limits, except for a mildly elevated HbA1c (6.2%), indicating impaired glucose metabolism or prediabetes. Renal function, electrolytes, and lipid profile are within reference ranges. Recommend clinical correlation for glycemic control and consideration of lifestyle modification or further evaluation for diabetes risk.
